cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.DM

The paper deals with automata and logics for nested words, which are a topic in formal language theory (FL) and logic (LO). It also introduces weighted models for quantitative systems, which are a topic in data structures (DS) and programming languages (PL). Finally, it discusses the expressive power of the logics and automata, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (DM). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.FL and cs.LO, followed by cs.DS, cs.PL, and cs.DM.
